texts.orig: Okay, so you've verified that the correct admin password is being used, but you still can't login? Most likely the account has been locked out. You can reset the account by running the following SQL statement:
texts.text: Okay, so you've verified that the correct admin password is being used, but you still can't login? Most likely the account has been locked out. You can reset the account by running the following SQL statement:

texts.label: code
texts.orig: echo "use psa; truncate lockout;" | mysql -u root -p\`cat /etc/psa/.psa.shadow\`
